cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the issue of sample selection bias and covariate shift, which are common problems in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes novel algorithms for estimating unknown training examples, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The experiments conducted in the paper involve various ML models and datasets, indicating that it could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
